, Wing; 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FDBDD3AEFDD32EEC" bold="true" box="[612,637,1942,1966]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">99</emphasis>
, Abdomen, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FCA4D3AEFC0D2EEC" bold="true" box="[893,931,1942,1966]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">100</emphasis>
, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FAA9D3AEFA382EEC" bold="true" box="[1392,1430,1942,1966]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">101</emphasis>
, Terminalia, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FE4ED382FE132E90" bold="true" box="[407,445,1978,2002]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">102</emphasis>
, Left surstylus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FD32D382FCBF2E90" bold="true" box="[747,785,1978,2002]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">103</emphasis>
, Right surstylus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FB95D382FBDC2E90" bold="true" box="[1100,1138,1978,2002]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">104</emphasis>
, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FEF9D3E6FEE82EB4" bold="true" box="[288,326,2014,2038]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">105</emphasis>
, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD94844FCD2D3E6FC9F2EB4" bold="true" box="[779,817,2014,2038]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">106</emphasis>
, Ejaculatory apodeme.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFD84845FF1ED4AEFEA02BB3" blockId="19.[151,1437,150,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FF1ED4AEFE4629F2" bold="true" box="[199,488,150,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Intraspecific variability.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B6A3DDBFFD84845FE36D4AEFD2529F2" author="Rafael, J. A." box="[495,651,150,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" pagination="353 - 390" refId="ref19665" refString="Rafael, J. A. (1990) Revisao das especies neotropicais do genero Cephalops Fallen (Diptera: Pipunculidae). Acta Amazonica, 20, 353 - 390." type="journal article" year="1990">Rafael (1990)</bibRefCitation>
provided a complete description and illustrations of the Brazilian 
<typeStatus id="9040FE88FFD84845FAAED4AEFF4F2996" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">holotype</typeStatus>
; however, we found variations in the Colombian material. Because of this, we provide a comparison of the variations between the Colombian and Brazilian specimens (between parenthesis, when comparable). MALE. Length with 
<quantity id="8803EDCFFFD84845FEF4D53AFE28285F" box="[301,390,258,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FE40D53BFE4F285E" box="[409,481,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">versus</emphasis>
<quantity id="8803EDCFFFD84845FE33D53AFDEA285F" box="[490,580,258,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
in the 
<typeStatus id="9040FE88FFD84845FD40D53AFCAE285F" box="[665,768,258,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">holotype</typeStatus>
); postcranium gray pruinose laterally and brown pruinose dorsally (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FEDBD51EFE292803" box="[258,391,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Figs 94–95</figureCitation>
); pedicel brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FD94D51EFD0E2803" box="[589,672,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FD63D51FFCAC2802" box="[698,770,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">versus</emphasis>
pedicel black); scutum and scutellum brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FAC8D51EFA3A2802" box="[1297,1428,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Figs 95, 97</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FF78D573FF472826" box="[161,233,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">versus</emphasis>
scutum and scutellum black); wing with membrane slightly brown infuscate (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FBBBD572FB192826" box="[1122,1207,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
); coxae brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FAB6D572FF1A28CA" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FF16D557FEB928CA" box="[207,279,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">versus</emphasis>
coxae black); trochanters light brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FD00D556FC8228CA" box="[729,812,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FC9ED557FC2128CA" box="[839,911,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">versus</emphasis>
trochanters yellow); femora yellow, except in proximal third, light yellow, and short setae ventrally (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FD36D5AAFCC128EF" box="[751,879,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Figs 94–95</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FC5CD5ABFC6328EE" box="[901,973,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">versus</emphasis>
femora entirely yellow, and without setae ventrally); tibiae light brown, with bases and apices light yellow, with a row of long and fine yellow setae posterolaterally (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FF3FD5E2FE9428B6" box="[230,314,474,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
); tergites 3–5 dark brown, shiny, with inconspicuous scattered setae (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FBE2D5E2FB4A28B6" box="[1083,1252,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Figs 94–95, 99</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFD84845FB25D5E3FAEA28B6" box="[1276,1348,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">versus</emphasis>
tergites 3–4 with narrow posterior band dark brown to black pruinose); tergites and sternites 6 and 7 as in 
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FB03D5C6FA942B5A" box="[1242,1338,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
. Surstyli asymmetrical, shorter than epandrium, completely setose, both surstyli with a lobe on inner margin, left surstylus slightly shorter and thin (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FE6DD67EFDB82B22" box="[436,534,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
); both surstyli with tips acute and downward directed when seen in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FF46D652FE932BC6" box="[159,317,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Figs 102–103</figureCitation>
); gonopods subsymmetrical, right gonopod slightly thinner than left (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FBE7D652FB0E2BC6" box="[1086,1184,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
); apex of phallic guide short, with acute tip and distinct submedian lobe dorsally, backwards directed (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FBD3D6B6FBC22BEB" box="[1034,1132,654,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 105</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory apodeme pinshaped, with margins somewhat straight (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FDB1D68AFD652B8F" box="[616,715,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
); phallus unbranched, with leaf-shaped membranous projections (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFD84845FF79D6EEFEAC2BB3" box="[160,258,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–106" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-30@18.[181,1406,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 94–106. Cephalops inpaganus (IAvH–M100905). Male. 94, Habitus, left lateral view; 95, Habitus, dorsal view; 96, Antenna; 97, Thorax, dorsal view; 98, Wing; 99, Abdomen, dorsal view; 100, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 101, Terminalia, dorsal view; 102, Left surstylus, lateral view; 103, Right surstylus, lateral view; 104, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 105, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 106, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592682/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 105</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
